sql:
SELECT s.song_id, s.title
FROM songs s
WHERE s.song_id NOT IN (
  SELECT song_id FROM song_streams
)
AND s.song_id NOT IN (
  SELECT song_id FROM song_genres
);

external_knowledge:
- "chart-topping waves" metaphorically refers to highly streamed songs;
- "cast their nets into the sea of sound" is a metaphor for artists creating music;
- "crashed upon the shores of a hundred thousand listeners or more" indicates that the songs must have been streamed more than 100,000 times;
- "types of musical currents" refers to musical genres.

sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS avg_rating 
FROM song_ratings 
WHERE song_id = 'specific_song_id';

external_knowledge:
- "stars and their musical territories" refers to artists and their genres;
- "blossomed in the new millennium" refers to artists formed after the year 2000;
- "over a decade's worth of hits" signifies having more than 10 songs;
- "significant presence in the streaming and download realms" refers to sources of revenue;
- "all measured in US dollars" means the currency of the revenue is USD.

sql:
SELECT artists.name AS identity, artist_socials.handle AS online_alias
FROM artists
JOIN artist_socials ON artists.artist_id = artist_socials.artist_id;

SELECT song_id, COUNT(user_id) AS total_ratings
FROM song_ratings
GROUP BY song_id;
